modules.description: The module provides functions to generate and manipulate UUIDs across multiple versions, including name-based hashing (MD5, SHA-1 for v3/v5), random generation (v4), time-and-random hybrids (v7), and custom formats (v8). It operates on UUID values (`Uuidm.t`), strings, byte sequences, and integer timestamps, offering utilities for parsing, serialization, and introspection such as extracting version/variant fields or converting timestamps. This supports use cases like distributed systems requiring unique identifiers (v4), deterministic UUIDs from namespaced data (v3/v5), ordered time-based identifiers (v7), and domain-specific custom formats (v8), with attention to endianness and string representation.
